  "abstract": "In India as in the rest of theworld, climate change has become\r\nnot just a cause for concern but also a call to urgent and\r\nspecific action. It's increasingly likely that our descendants\r\nwill face a less stable,more violent climate. They will have to\r\nbecome resilient against extreme droughts, floods, storms and\r\nheat. Resilience is especially important in the rainfed\r\ndrylands,where highly variable rainfall flips agriculture from\r\nboom to bust over short time periods.\r\nFollowing Hurricane Sandy's recent devastation, Andrew\r\nZolli summed up resilience strategy thus: “Where\r\nsustainability aims to put the world back into balance,\r\nresilience looks for ways tomanage in an imbalancedworld.”\r\nHe used the metaphor of “rolling with the waves, instead of\r\ntrying to stop the ocean.”...",
